Title: Connection of Olympic College to NSFnet
Co-PIName(s): Larry Ryan, Ruth Ross, Kevin Blackwell
Abstract: Olympic College is establishing a connection to NSFNET via a               56,000 bits per second line through the NorthWestNet mid-level                  network.  The connection enables the school's faculty and students              to communicate and collaborate with the international scientific                and educational community, and to access network resources such as              libraries, databases and supercomputers.  This award funds part of              the  costs for two years.
